  "prompt": "What should be my 12th board percentage to get admission in St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for B.Com?",
  "response": "Admission criteria for St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai can vary from year to year and may depend on several factors including the number of applicants, quota systems, and other considerations. However, generally speaking, you should aim for a high percentage in your 12th board exams to increase your chances of securing admission to competitive programs like B.Com.\n\nTypically, a score of above 85% in your 12th grade exams would be considered competitive, but aiming for 90% or higher will improve your chances significantly, especially if you are applying under the general category. Additionally, it's important to check if there are any specific cut-off percentages or additional requirements set by the college for the year you are applying.\n\nI recommend checking the official St. Xavier's College website or contacting their admissions office directly to get the most accurate and updated information regarding the admission criteria for the B.Com program.",
